update stops
set body = 'Randall County was established by the Texas Legislature in 1876, carved out of the vast Bexar District as settlement pushed onto the high plains following the Red River War. Canyon was named the county seat when the county formally organized in 1889, and a modest frame courthouse served the early community. By 1909, with the town growing around the newly arrived Santa Fe Railway, Randall County commissioned this two-story Classical Revival structure as a permanent statement of civic confidence. The building features pressed brick construction, decorative cornices, and a symmetrical facade typical of county courthouses built across Texas during that era. A new Randall County Justice Center was completed in the 1990s, but the 1909 building remains standing on the square and is the subject of an ongoing restoration effort led by the Randall County Historical Commission.'
where name = '1909 Randall County Courthouse';
